## AI Workflow

Selected workflow: `{{.Workflow}}`

{{- if eq .Workflow "auto"}}
This project uses a persistent 4-agent workflow with file-based coordination. Four roles (Planner, Implementer, Reviewer, Tester) communicate through shared files in `.ai/` and follow a defined task status flow.
{{- else}}
This project uses a persistent 3-agent workflow with file-based coordination. Three roles (Planner, Implementer, Reviewer) communicate through shared files in `.ai/` and follow a defined task status flow.
{{- end}}

### Concepts

**Cycle** — a unit of work on a feature branch. One cycle = one branch = one PR.

**Roles and file ownership:**

| Role | Reads | Writes |
|------|-------|--------|
| Planner | `ROADMAP.md` | `.ai/PLAN.md`, `.ai/TASKS.md` |
| Implementer | `.ai/PLAN.md`, `.ai/REVIEW.md` | source code, `.ai/TASKS.md` |
| Reviewer | `.ai/PLAN.md`, commits | `.ai/REVIEW.md`, `.ai/TASKS.md` |
{{- if eq .Workflow "auto"}}
| Tester | `.ai/PLAN.md`, commits | `.ai/TEST_REPORT.md`, `.ai/TASKS.md` |
{{- end}}

**Status flow:**

{{- if eq .Workflow "auto"}}
```
in_planning → ready_for_implement → in_implementation → ready_for_review → in_review → in_testing → test_passed → done
                                          ↑                                     |                        |
                                          └──── changes_requested ◄─────────────┘                        |
                                                ▲                                                         |
                                                └──────────────────────── test_failed ◄───────────────────┘
```
{{- else}}
```
in_planning → ready_for_implement → in_implementation → ready_for_review → in_review → done
                                          ↑                                     |
                                          └──── changes_requested ◄─────────────┘
```
{{- end}}

### Start a new development cycle

```bash
# Edit ROADMAP.md with your goals first, then:
scripts/ai-start-cycle.sh feature/<scope>
```

### Start persistent role sessions

```bash
scripts/ai-plan.sh          # terminal 1
scripts/ai-implement.sh     # terminal 2
scripts/ai-review.sh        # terminal 3
{{- if eq .Workflow "auto"}}
scripts/ai-test.sh          # terminal 4
{{- end}}
```

Launch each role once, then keep those sessions open for the rest of the cycle.

### Drive work inside the existing sessions

```text
planner> start_plan
implementer> next_task T-001
reviewer> next_task T-001
{{- if eq .Workflow "auto"}}
tester> next_task T-001
{{- end}}
implementer> rework_task T-001
reviewer> finish_cycle
```

**Planner commands:**

| Command | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| `start_plan` | Read `ROADMAP.md`, write `.ai/PLAN.md` and `.ai/TASKS.md` |
| `rework_plan [TASK_ID]` | Revisit the plan when scope or approach changes |

**Implementer commands:**

| Command | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| `next_task [TASK_ID]` | Pick up the next `ready_for_implement` task |
| `rework_task [TASK_ID]` | Address `changes_requested` findings |
| `status_cycle [TASK_ID]` | Show task status and recommended next action |

**Reviewer commands:**

| Command | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| `next_task [TASK_ID]` | Pick up the next `ready_for_review` task |
| `status_cycle [TASK_ID]` | Show task status and recommended next action |
{{- if eq .Workflow "auto"}}
| `finish_cycle [TASK_ID]` | Close the cycle after all tasks reach `test_passed` or `done` |
{{- else}}
| `finish_cycle [TASK_ID]` | Close the cycle after all tasks reach `done` |
{{- end}}

{{- if eq .Workflow "auto"}}
**Tester commands:**

| Command | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| `next_task [TASK_ID]` | Pick up the next `in_testing` task |
| `status_cycle [TASK_ID]` | Show task status and recommended next action |
{{- end}}

### File map

| File | Purpose | Tracked |
|------|---------|---------|
| `.ai/PLAN.md` | Current plan | yes |
| `.ai/TASKS.md` | Task board with status | yes |
| `.ai/REVIEW.md` | Review findings | yes |
{{- if eq .Workflow "auto"}}
| `.ai/TEST_REPORT.md` | Test findings | yes |
{{- end}}
| `.ai/HANDOFF.md` | Runtime handoff log | no |
| `ROADMAP.md` | Cycle goals (edit before planning) | yes |
| `CLAUDE.md` | Agent rules and validation | yes |

### Create a PR

```bash
scripts/ai-pr.sh sync
```

Full workflow details and session recovery rules are in `CLAUDE.md`.
